WEBVTT

00:01.635 --> 00:03.469
[ Quacking ]

00:03.504 --> 00:04.803
[ Warble, zap! ]

00:09.310 --> 00:10.476
[ Roars ]

00:12.413 --> 00:13.512
♪ "Adventure Time"

00:13.547 --> 00:14.880
♪ Come on, grab your friends

00:14.915 --> 00:17.683
♪ We'll go to very
distant lands ♪

00:17.718 --> 00:18.917
♪ With Jake the Dog
and Finn the Human ♪

00:20.221 --> 00:21.553
♪ The fun will never end

00:21.589 --> 00:23.589
♪ It's "Adventure Time"

00:30.931 --> 00:33.999
Vroom, vroom!

00:34.001 --> 00:36.068
Vroom, vroom, vroom!

00:36.070 --> 00:37.870
Tree Trunks: Sweet P!

00:37.872 --> 00:38.871
[ Gasps ]

00:41.142 --> 00:44.009
Come and get it,
Sweet P.

00:44.011 --> 00:45.377
Oh, boy!

00:45.379 --> 00:47.713
Breakfast porridge.

00:52.853 --> 00:54.620
Mmm.

00:54.622 --> 00:59.758
I think I must have the most
perfect life in the whole world.

00:59.760 --> 01:01.827
Oh, that's lovely.

01:01.829 --> 01:03.328
What about you, Mama?

01:03.330 --> 01:05.631
Is your life perfect?

01:05.633 --> 01:07.966
Me?

01:07.968 --> 01:11.170
♪

01:15.810 --> 01:17.309
Yes, Sweet P.

01:17.311 --> 01:21.013
I'm the happiest mama
in the whole world.

01:21.015 --> 01:22.848
Oh, no, Mama!

01:22.850 --> 01:24.283
You're sad!

01:24.285 --> 01:25.451
No, no, sweetie.

01:25.453 --> 01:26.985
That's just something
that happens

01:26.987 --> 01:30.556
when grown-ups think about
their lives for too long.

01:30.558 --> 01:31.623
[ Telephone ringing ]

01:31.625 --> 01:33.492
Mr. Pig:
Honey, can you get that?

01:33.494 --> 01:35.861
Thanks, sweetie.

01:37.731 --> 01:39.331
Hello?

01:39.333 --> 01:40.466
Tree Trunks?

01:40.468 --> 01:42.367
Tree Trunks,
it's me, Randy.

01:42.369 --> 01:45.137
Wow, it's so great
to hear your voice.

01:45.139 --> 01:46.405
Randy?

01:46.407 --> 01:48.207
Forgive me
for being so bold,

01:48.209 --> 01:49.942
but Tree Trunks,
I must see you.

01:49.944 --> 01:53.979
I don't think that's
a very good idea, Randy.

01:53.981 --> 01:55.347
Tree Trunks, please!

01:55.349 --> 01:58.517
Um, okay, hold on.

01:59.386 --> 02:01.186
Who was that,
sweetie?

02:01.188 --> 02:03.856
That was,
uh, the school.

02:03.858 --> 02:08.727
There's a parent-teacher
conference I need to go to.

02:08.729 --> 02:11.463
Really?
Isn't it my turn this time?

02:11.465 --> 02:13.866
No, because, um...

02:15.836 --> 02:17.436
...it's my turn?

02:17.438 --> 02:19.138
Well,
if you say so.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.106
Be back soon.

02:21.108 --> 02:22.141
Okay.

02:22.143 --> 02:24.009
Uh, bye.

02:26.147 --> 02:29.348
♪

02:30.618 --> 02:32.751
[ Bike bell rings ]

02:34.088 --> 02:36.388
The future's wild.

02:44.398 --> 02:47.599
♪

02:51.372 --> 02:52.838
We did it, babe.

02:52.840 --> 02:55.240
We finally graduated
high school.

02:55.242 --> 02:58.143
Yes, Randy, we did.

02:58.145 --> 02:59.778
[ Clears throat ]

02:59.780 --> 03:02.347
Tree Trunks,
would you sign my yearbook?

03:02.349 --> 03:04.082
I sure will, Cookie.

03:04.084 --> 03:07.452
Do you want me to sign
on my fencing photo,

03:07.454 --> 03:09.655
my Homecoming Queen photo,

03:09.657 --> 03:11.790
my horseback riding club
photo --

03:11.792 --> 03:13.492
Would you sign
your swim team photo?

03:13.494 --> 03:16.028
Yes.
That's my favorite.

03:16.030 --> 03:19.198
When you get done with that
kid stuff, let me know.

03:19.200 --> 03:20.666
I got grown-up stuff
to discuss.

03:20.668 --> 03:25.170
I was about to say
the same thing to you.

03:25.172 --> 03:29.408
Randy, I've decided to
take some time for myself

03:29.410 --> 03:30.876
and see the world.

03:30.878 --> 03:35.447
I'm 18 and I need adventure,
Randy.

03:35.449 --> 03:37.316
I need --

03:37.318 --> 03:39.117
What?

03:39.119 --> 03:40.185
Baby...

03:40.187 --> 03:41.320
[ Gasps ]

03:41.322 --> 03:43.255
...let me
be your adventure.

03:43.257 --> 03:45.224
Okay, why not?

03:45.226 --> 03:46.525
[ Camera shutter flashes ]

03:50.130 --> 03:52.397
Kiss her, son!

03:52.399 --> 03:55.167
[ Camera shutter flashes ]

03:55.169 --> 03:56.668
Our wedding photos
are here.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.503
Just in time
for the honeymoon.

03:58.505 --> 03:59.571
Babe?

03:59.573 --> 04:01.406
It's over, Randy.

04:01.408 --> 04:04.076
I'm a wild child.

04:07.982 --> 04:10.249
Goodbye.

04:10.251 --> 04:13.385
"Goodbye, Randy."

04:13.387 --> 04:15.153
[ Chuckles ]

04:15.155 --> 04:16.722
-Okay.
-Hmm?

04:16.724 --> 04:20.559
Oh, Randy, I'm so sorry
you went to all this trouble.

04:20.561 --> 04:23.128
-Huh?
-I mean, I'm flattered,

04:23.130 --> 04:27.633
but I have a family now
and I can't run away with you.

04:27.635 --> 04:31.103
That -- Tree Trunks,
that's not why I asked you here.

04:31.105 --> 04:32.437
It's not?

04:32.439 --> 04:36.074
No. I just wanted to ask you
for my grandmother's ring back.

04:36.076 --> 04:37.576
Oh.

04:37.578 --> 04:39.978
I'm going to propose to
my girlfriend this weekend.

04:39.980 --> 04:41.980
I've got the chocolate
and the flowers,

04:41.982 --> 04:43.615
but I need that ring.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.217
Well, I'm sorry,

04:45.219 --> 04:48.854
but I threw that ring
down a bottomless pit.

04:48.856 --> 04:50.055
Oh, no!

04:50.057 --> 04:52.157
No, wait,
that's not right.

04:52.159 --> 04:56.428
I used that ring to propose
to my second husband, Danny.

04:56.430 --> 04:58.297
Oh, no.

04:58.299 --> 05:01.600
Oh, Danny.

05:01.602 --> 05:06.571
At sea,
I made a new life for myself.

05:08.309 --> 05:10.108
Mr. Faidutti.

05:10.110 --> 05:12.010
Yes,
Captain Tree Trunks.

05:12.012 --> 05:17.549
Mr. Faidutti,
pick up that mop, you bug.

05:21.588 --> 05:23.422
Mm-hmm.

05:23.424 --> 05:24.790
Captain Tree Trunks,

05:24.792 --> 05:27.092
we're approaching a ship
off the port bow!

05:27.094 --> 05:29.328
Good.

05:29.330 --> 05:32.831
Drown all
but the tightest men.

05:32.833 --> 05:35.033
-No!
-Impudence.

05:35.035 --> 05:37.803
I beg of you, madam,
while I am tight,

05:37.805 --> 05:41.006
my brother is not,
and yet I love him.

05:41.008 --> 05:42.240
Hmm.

05:42.242 --> 05:43.642
My name is Daniel Prince

05:43.644 --> 05:45.510
and this is my brother,
Peanut.

05:45.512 --> 05:47.179
Please look into your heart
and pity him,

05:47.181 --> 05:49.481
for though our family
is quite wealthy,

05:49.483 --> 05:51.550
he has had
a difficult life.

05:51.552 --> 05:53.118
You are a very beautiful
elephant,

05:53.120 --> 05:55.754
but I fear your bandit ways
have made you hard.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.956
He was right.

05:57.958 --> 06:01.226
I left my post that very day

06:01.228 --> 06:05.731
so that I could spend
the rest of my life with Danny.

06:05.733 --> 06:08.834
[ Smooching ]

06:08.836 --> 06:12.270
That evening,
we were wed.

06:12.272 --> 06:15.941
[ Mumbling incoherently ]

06:15.943 --> 06:17.309
Peanut?

06:17.311 --> 06:18.410
Kiss my mouth, baby!

06:18.412 --> 06:19.511
Yeah.

06:19.513 --> 06:21.913
[ Smooching ]

06:21.915 --> 06:26.284
Tree Trunks: My joy, however,
would be short-lived.

06:26.286 --> 06:28.186
Was Danny smooth?

06:28.188 --> 06:29.321
Yes.

06:29.323 --> 06:31.123
Was Danny tight?

06:31.125 --> 06:32.290
Yes.

06:32.292 --> 06:34.693
But was he a liar?

06:34.695 --> 06:37.329
Yes, yes, yes!

06:37.331 --> 06:38.897
[ Screeches ]

06:38.899 --> 06:42.701
A liar in cahoots
with Mr. Faidutti

06:42.703 --> 06:44.936
to get me away
from my ship.

06:46.039 --> 06:48.673
I marooned Danny,

06:48.675 --> 06:51.777
and I kaboomed Mr. Faidutti.

06:54.681 --> 06:58.750
No more tight men.

06:58.752 --> 07:03.622
That Danny was really,
really, really something.

07:03.624 --> 07:04.823
Okay, I get it.

07:04.825 --> 07:06.158
But what about the ring?

07:06.160 --> 07:07.225
What happened next?

07:07.227 --> 07:11.663
I savvily invested
my pirate treasure

07:11.665 --> 07:15.267
and became a powerful
shipping magnate.

07:18.038 --> 07:20.572
[ Knock on door ]

07:23.510 --> 07:26.044
Come in.

07:27.281 --> 07:31.149
Uh, I'm Wyatt,
your new secretary.

07:31.151 --> 07:36.221
These flowers are from
Robot Body Moe.

07:36.223 --> 07:37.956
Oh, again?

07:37.958 --> 07:41.259
Throw those
in the trash.

07:41.261 --> 07:43.695
Okay, ma'am.

07:46.800 --> 07:49.067
They're a little --
a little big.

07:49.069 --> 07:50.368
Oh, boy.

07:50.370 --> 07:53.338
The other way,
like a vase.

07:53.340 --> 07:57.275
[ Groaning ]

07:57.277 --> 07:59.711
[ Sobbing ]

07:59.713 --> 08:02.714
He melted my heart.

08:04.017 --> 08:06.084
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:06.086 --> 08:07.819
Hey-hey!

08:10.023 --> 08:12.224
Somebody kiss me now!

08:13.560 --> 08:15.160
Tree Trunks:
I sold the company

08:15.162 --> 08:18.864
and gave all my money
to the King of Ooo.

08:18.866 --> 08:22.567
Swim with me, Wyatt,
you sweet boy.

08:22.569 --> 08:24.336
Oh, uh --

08:24.338 --> 08:28.006
[ Laughs ]
I'm never wearing clothes again!

08:28.008 --> 08:31.843
I, uh,
might keep my shirt on.

08:31.845 --> 08:35.847
I thought
Glob had told me,

08:35.849 --> 08:38.250
"Here's someone
who needs your love."

08:38.252 --> 08:40.819
But what he really
must've said was,

08:40.821 --> 08:43.688
"Go suck an egg,
Tree Trunks."

08:45.726 --> 08:47.726
No more pie.

08:47.728 --> 08:50.028
But that's my pie.

08:50.030 --> 08:53.865
You're draining
my life away.

08:53.867 --> 08:56.635
Take care of me!

08:56.637 --> 09:00.238
No. You've emptied me
of my joie de vivre.

09:00.240 --> 09:01.973
[ Groaning ]

09:01.975 --> 09:03.675
I've got the ring!

09:03.677 --> 09:08.113
If I don't give it back,
it means we're still in love!

09:08.115 --> 09:11.049
I'm throwing it
in a bottomless pit!

09:11.051 --> 09:13.718
Wyatt
threw my ring in a pit?

09:13.720 --> 09:16.555
Yeah,
sorry about that.

09:16.557 --> 09:18.590
Uh -- huh?

09:18.592 --> 09:20.325
Aah!

09:20.327 --> 09:22.127
[ Grunts ]

09:22.129 --> 09:23.562
[ Groans ]

09:23.564 --> 09:26.231
Mr. Pig,
what are you doing here?

09:26.233 --> 09:28.967
I followed you because
I was afraid that --

09:28.969 --> 09:30.569
And now I see you.

09:30.571 --> 09:31.970
Oh, no.

09:31.972 --> 09:34.039
I just wanted
my grandma's ring back.

09:34.041 --> 09:38.476
And I just didn't want you
to worry over nothing.

09:38.478 --> 09:40.378
R-Really?

09:40.380 --> 09:41.813
Oh, geez.

09:41.815 --> 09:43.848
Wyatt: There you are!

09:44.785 --> 09:47.118
How could you,
Tree Trunks?

09:47.120 --> 09:49.955
Wyatt?
You've been following me?

09:49.957 --> 09:51.590
You wish, babe.

09:51.592 --> 09:54.392
I've been following him
to you!

09:54.394 --> 09:57.929
But if Tree Trunks is gonna be
stepping out on her man

09:57.931 --> 10:02.801
with one of her exes,
it's gonna be me!

10:04.471 --> 10:05.937
[ Groans ]

10:05.939 --> 10:08.473
Tree Trunks, help me.

10:08.475 --> 10:10.241
I need you.

10:10.243 --> 10:11.743
My ring!

10:11.745 --> 10:13.945
Just give me...
-[ Groaning ]

10:13.947 --> 10:16.047
My suck-suck ring.

10:16.049 --> 10:18.283
Aha!
Gotcha!

10:18.285 --> 10:19.651
[ Laughs ]

10:19.653 --> 10:21.353
[ Groans ]

10:21.355 --> 10:23.588
Um, I'm sorry
I didn't trust you.

10:23.590 --> 10:26.424
I just know you've had
a lot of adventures in the past

10:26.426 --> 10:28.393
and things are
kind of boring now.

10:28.395 --> 10:29.427
It's true.

10:29.429 --> 10:32.397
I sometimes miss
those wild times,

10:32.399 --> 10:36.101
but back then, I couldn't even
tell the difference

10:36.103 --> 10:39.437
between a good adventure
and a bad one.

10:39.439 --> 10:45.076
I was just a leaf in the wind,
blown about by my whims.

10:45.078 --> 10:48.446
But now
I'm on solid ground.

10:48.448 --> 10:52.917
You and Sweet P
are my -- uh --

10:52.919 --> 10:54.753
Your greatest adventure?

10:54.755 --> 10:56.955
Yeah.

10:56.957 --> 10:57.822
Whoa, what the?

10:58.358 --> 10:59.724
Is that Wyatt?

10:59.726 --> 11:01.226
Tree Trunks?

11:01.228 --> 11:03.328
What the heck
is going on in here?
